This guide [[Article description::explains how to install and run MathWorks Matlab on Gentoo.]]

== Mounting the installation media ==

=== ISO file ===

{{RootCmd
|modprobe loop
|mkdir -p /mnt/iso
|mount -o loop matlab.iso /mnt/iso
|cd /mnt/iso
}}

=== Optical disk ===

{{RootCmd
|mkdir -p /mnt/cdrom
|mount -t iso9660 -o ro /dev/cdrom /mnt/cdrom
|cd /mnt/cdrom
}}

== Installing ==

{{RootCmd
|./install
}}

== Troubleshooting ==

=== Blank window while using xmonad/awesome/dwm ===

Set the WM name to "LG3D"

e.g. xmonad:

{{FileBox|filename=~/.xmonad/xmonad.hs|1=
main =
    xmonad $ defaultConfig {
      startupHook = setWMName "LG3D"
    }
}}

